- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the computation of Grobner bases, which is a central topic in symbolic computation. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the time-complexity of the algorithm and provides numerical examples to illustrate it. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as tropical geometry is a subfield of algebraic geometry, which has connections to computational geometry. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of the FGLM algorithm, which is commonly used in control theory. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the theory of Grobner bases, which has connections to logic and automated reasoning.
